d occupation, which destroyed the town and forced uneasy co-existence between civilians and militants.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aWar and societyzSierra Leone. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aafrica.  aanthropologists.  aanthropology.  acivilians.  acultural memory.  aethnographies.  aevangelists.  afathers.  agovernment.  ahuman impact.  alife and death.  amakeni.  amilitants.  amilitary history.  amodern history.  anonfiction accounts.  aovercoming trauma.  apersonal stories.  apolitical.  apoliticians.  apower of love.  arebel forces.  arebels.  asierra leone.  asierra leoneans.  asocial justice.  asocial world.  asoldiers.  astudents.  asurvival.  atraders.  atraumatic experiences.  atrue stories.  aviolence.  awartime experiences.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095353640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953536423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953536/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles